apiValueDetail.apiDesc:

Ignored on Apple Maps

apiValue.shortdesc: Enables or disables the compass.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc:
Enables or disables the compass. The compass is an icon on the map that indicates the direction of north on the map.
If enabled, it is only shown when the camera is rotated away from its default orientation (bearing of 0). When a user taps the compass, the camera orients itself to its default orientation and fades away shortly after. If disabled, the compass will never be displayed.

apiValue.shortdesc: Controls whether gestures by users are completely consumed by the GMSMapView when gestures are enabled (default true).

apiValueDetail.apiDesc:
Controls whether gestures by users are completely consumed by the GMSMapView when gestures are enabled (default true). This prevents these gestures from being received by parent views.
When the GMSMapView is contained by a UIScrollView (or other scrollable area), this means that gestures on the map will not be additional consumed as scroll gestures. However, disabling this (set to NO) may be useful to support complex view hierarchies or requirements.
Ignored on Apple Maps

apiValue.shortdesc: Enables (default) or disables the indoor floor picker.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc:
Enables (default) or disables the indoor floor picker. If enabled, it is only visible when the view is focused on a building with indoor floor data. If disabled, the selected floor can still be controlled programmatically via the indoorDisplay mapView property.
Ignored on Apple Maps

apiValue.shortdesc: Sets the preference for whether the Map Toolbar should be enabled or disabled.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc:
Sets the preference for whether the Map Toolbar should be enabled or disabled. If enabled, and the Map Toolbar can be shown in the current context, users will see a bar with various context-dependent actions, including 'open this map in the Google Maps app' and 'find directions to the highlighted marker in the Google Maps app' (default true).
Ignored on Apple Maps

apiValue.shortdesc: Enables or disables the My Location button.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Enables or disables the My Location button. This is a button visible on the map that, when tapped by users, will center the map on the current user location.

apiValue.shortdesc: Controls whether rotate gestures are enabled (default) or disabled.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Controls whether rotate gestures are enabled (default) or disabled. If enabled, users may use a two-finger rotate gesture to rotate the camera. This does not limit programmatic control of the camera's bearing.

apiValue.shortdesc: Controls whether scroll gestures are enabled (default) or disabled.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Controls whether scroll gestures are enabled (default) or disabled. If enabled, users may drag to pan the camera. This does not limit programmatic movement of the camera.

apiValue.shortdesc: Controls whether tilt gestures are enabled (default) or disabled.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Controls whether tilt gestures are enabled (default) or disabled. If enabled, users may use a two-finger vertical down or up swipe to tilt the camera. This does not limit programmatic control of the camera's viewingAngle.

apiValue.shortdesc: Controls whether zoom gestures are enabled (default) or disabled.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: Controls whether zoom gestures are enabled (default) or disabled. If enabled, users may double tap/two-finger tap or pinch to zoom the camera. This does not limit programmatic movement of the camera.

apiValue.shortdesc: The amount that the image should be rotated in a clockwise direction.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: The amount that the image should be rotated in a clockwise direction. The center of the rotation will be the image's anchor. This is optional and the default bearing is 0, i.e., the image is aligned so that up is north.

apiValue.shortdesc: If you want to handle events fired when the user clicks the ground overlay, set this property to true.

apiValueDetail.apiDesc: If you want to handle events fired when the user clicks the ground overlay, set this property to true. You can change this value at any time. The default is false.
